# The NoCloud datasource's instance identity. cloud-init runs its
# per-instance configuration (formatting the exports disk, installing
# packages) once for each instance-id, and never again. Because of
# this, editing user-data on a server that has already booted needs
# a new instance-id before the change takes effect. A cleaner option
# is a factory reset (make clean), since the whole point of this
# fixture is that it rebuilds itself from the seed.
instance-id: liken-lab-storage-1
local-hostname: storage
